      },
      {
        "quote": "‘They say the whole Empire will eventually float by if you sit by the Reik long enough. Well, I’ve sat here, rod in hand, for twenty years, watching the flow downriver. The things I could tell you. I’ve seen war and I’ve seen peace. I’ve seen good times and bad. I’ve seen happiness and sorrow. And in all that time, I can honestly say, I’ve not caught a single bloody fish.’",
        "source": "– Thys Lange, the Reikland’s worst Fisherman"
      }
    ],
    "adventuring": "A Riverwoman will feel at home on any stretch of water, and their skills ensure they can drop everything, confident that they will be able to find work elsewhere should they need to. A Riverwoman is well-placed to get the lowdown on the more iniquitous side of river life and may have contacts among the river’s lowlifes. With their knowledge and experience they can make all the difference to a water-based expedition or investigation."
  }
}

